        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 18 at 5:57PM EDT until June 18 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Battle Creek to 6 miles south of Homer, moving
northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall, Battle Creek, Homer, Brownlee Park and Albion.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain alert for a possible tornado! Tornadoes can develop quickly
from severe thunderstorms. If you spot a tornado go at once into the
basement or small central room in a sturdy structure.</instruction>
